# F1 Backend API

Personal F1 data backend â€” race results, qualifying, sprint, live timing.

Built with **FastAPI** + **APScheduler** + **OpenF1** + **Jolpica**.

---

## Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| API server | FastAPI + uvicorn |
| Live data | OpenF1 REST API |
| Calendar / Results | Jolpica (Ergast fork) |
| Scheduler | APScheduler 3.x |
| Database | SQLite (aiosqlite) |

---

## Setup

```bash
# 1. Clone / navigate to project
cd f1-backend

# 2. Create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

# 3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 4. Configure environment
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env â€” add OPENF1_TOKEN if you have a sponsor tier account

# 5. Run
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000
```

The API will be live at `http://localhost:8000`
Auto-generated docs at `http://localhost:8000/docs`

---

## API Endpoints

### Schedule
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/schedule` | Full race calendar |
| GET | `/schedule?year=2025` | Calendar for a specific year |
| GET | `/schedule/next` | Next upcoming race weekend |
| GET | `/schedule/upcoming-sessions` | Sessions in the next 14 days |

### Live
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/live` | Live race snapshot (auto session key) |
| GET | `/live/{session_key}` | Live snapshot for specific session |

### Results
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/results/latest` | Latest race results |
| GET | `/results/latest?session_type=Qualifying` | Latest qualifying results |
| GET | `/results/{year}/{round}` | Results for specific round |
| GET | `/results/{year}/{round}?session_type=Sprint` | Sprint results |

### Standings
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/standings/drivers` | Driver championship standings |
| GET | `/standings/constructors` | Constructor standings |

### Session Details
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/sessions` | All sessions |
| GET | `/sessions/{session_key}/laps` | Lap times for a session |
| GET | `/sessions/{session_key}/fastest-laps` | Fastest lap per driver |
| GET | `/sessions/{session_key}/stints` | Tyre stints |
| GET | `/sessions/{session_key}/pit-stops` | Pit stops |
| GET | `/sessions/{session_key}/race-control` | Flags, SC, VSC messages |
| GET | `/sessions/{session_key}/weather` | Weather data |
| GET | `/sessions/{session_key}/drivers` | Driver info for session |

---

## Live Data

### Free tier (no token)
- Historical data works fully
- During a live session: polling still works but OpenF1 may rate-limit â€” works fine for personal use

### Sponsor tier (â‚¬9.90/mo)
- Add `OPENF1_TOKEN=your_token` to `.env`
- Enables true real-time via MQTT/WebSocket (future upgrade path)
- Higher rate limits

---

## How the Scheduler Works

On startup, the scheduler:
1. Pulls the race calendar from Jolpica
2. Finds all sessions within the next 14 days
3. Arms a **live polling job** (every 15s) to run during each session
4. Arms a **results fetch job** to run 15â€“30min after each session ends
5. Refreshes the schedule every Monday at 06:00 UTC

```
Session starts  â†’  live polling begins (every 15s) â†’ snapshots saved to DB
Session ends    â†’  results fetch fires after delay â†’ final results saved to DB
```

---

## Android App Integration

Your Android Java app just calls these endpoints via Retrofit:

```java
// Example: get live race state
Call<LiveSnapshot> getLive();

// Example: get latest race results  
Call<ResultsResponse> getLatestResults(@Query("session_type") String type);
```

Point Retrofit base URL at `http://your-server-ip:8000/`

---

## Deploying

For personal use, easiest options:
- **Raspberry Pi** on your home network
- **Railway.app** (free tier, easy Python deploy)
- **Render.com** (free tier)
- **Fly.io** (free tier)